Role Purpose
Bord Gais is a leading vertically integrated energy based in Ireland. Its activities cover the entire value chain: operation of upstream assets and management of energy supply contracts; optimisation activities performed by the midstream trade desks; supply of energy to downstream end users. Bord Gais is fully committed to meeting net zero targets both for itself and its customers and has already embarked upon this journey.
Reporting to the BGE Financial Risk Manager, the Senior Quantitative Risk Analyst is a key role within the Bord Gais Financial Risk team, which is tasked with the identification, quantification, and management of financial risks. The role entails responsibility for, and development of, sophisticated models and methodologies that quantify these risks and thereby provide a robust analytical platform for understanding the company’s risk profile. In addition, there will be a requirement to produce high calibre analysis to support the business on an ad-hoc basis.
The role will suit an analyst with quantitative modelling experience and demonstrable commercial acumen.
Location - UK or Ireland - Flexible / Home-based
Key accountabilities
The Senior Quantitative Risk Analyst will be responsible for:
Maintaining a suite of quantitative risk models & methodologies to produce regular reports and analysis for senior stakeholder, e.g. VaR (Value at Risk), Weather Risk, Commodity Exposures;
Measuring and quantifying risk across integrated BGE gas & electricity portfolios including the impact of hedging strategies and contractual arrangements on the portfolio;
Preparation of regular risk analysis utilising stochastic modelling techniques to critically challenge and back test existing and new risk management strategies;
Providing analytical insight in support of risk reviews of BGE originated transactions and new business proposals.
Communicating complex risk analysis and concepts to key senior stakeholders including BGE senior management and relevant risk review meetings (e.g. Financial Risk Committees)
Design/perform statistical studies of energy market prices for use in risk valuation and risk management decisions. Perform calibration of key model parameters (i.e. volatilities and correlations);
Application of strong model governance procedures to maintain the robustness of critical models;
Validating quantitative models and assumptions developed by Front Office teams;
Working with Centrica financial risk teams based in the UK to ensure the company is both utilising and sharing the latest risk modelling methodologies and techniques;
Supporting the wider team with the production and development of daily risk reports.
Person Specification
The successful candidate for the role will require:
Confidence, presence, resilience, and determination to succeed in a dynamic and demanding business environment;
Problem solving and root cause identification skills;
Excellent attention to detail;
Demonstrated communication skills, particularly of complex technical concepts to general audiences
Self-motivated, ability to prioritise work with minimal direction;
Team player prepared to help others achieve department goals.
Qualifications & Experience
Graduate degree in a highly analytical field (e.g. mathematics, statistics, economics, engineering, finance, etc.) from a reputable university;
Expertise in financial mathematics and/or other sophisticated quantitative techniques (e.g. Monte Carlo simulations, stochastic calculus, volatility and probability in finance and Econometric modelling techniques)
Experience in implementation of analytical tools using one of the following: Excel VBA, @Risk, MATLAB, R, Python, Power BI, as well as experience of working with large data sets;
Knowledge of energy markets is an advantage
