The opportunity
We have an opportunity for a business intelligence analyst to join our growing Business Consulting team. There are currently a number of career opportunities open at Consultant to Senior Consultant. This is an excellent opportunity to work as part of a fast paced, high growth Consulting team. Our team delivers consulting services in areas such as finance transformation, operational excellence, project and change management, strategy, digital and business transformation.
In Grant Thornton we promote a culture that invests in our employee's growth. Team members are supported from a cultural and professional perspective to continue to build on existing skillsets. The successful candidate will be offered the chance to undertake a number of development courses that complement their career path. Employees will be given the opportunity to work on jobs that align with their interests and expertise while gaining valuable experience from working on challenging and rewarding engagements.
In addition to a competitive base salary, successful candidates will be able to avail of our benefits packages which include discounted private health insurance, health and wellbeing services, a discounted gym membership, 2 company ‘gift days’ and summer working hours.
Essential duties and responsibilities
Identify, evaluate, and document potential data sources in support of project requirements;
Guide various business departments in appropriate and effective use of data;
Ability to take data and tell a story/display data in an engaging way;
Ingesting data from a variety of on premise and online data sources and performing required transformations;
Develop, design and build meaningful and insightful reports and dashboards using Microsoft Power BI;
Data modelling capabilities including designing effective BI data models;
Publishing reports via the Microsoft Power BI service, managing them using Power Apps and monitoring usage/data refreshes/security access;
Gather requirements for analytical reports;
Using data analytics tools and techniques to identify patterns, extract outliers, and perform analyses to address client problems;
Testing and validating solutions;
Experience conducting quantitative and qualitative analysis with visualisation and analytics techniques to solve defined business problems; and
Keeping abreast of developments across the data and analytics landscape, with the desire to translate the latest techniques and technologies into our project outputs.
Required skills/attributes
A Bachelor or Master’s Degree in a quantitative field (Operation Research, Computer Science, Engineering, Applied Math, Economics, Statistics, Analytics, Management/Business Information Systems (or related degree));
Logical thinking and ability to solve complex problems using analytical skills;
Ability to translate raw data into meaningful dashboards and reports;
Experience extracting, transforming and loading of datasets (ETL);
Ability to work with non-technical colleagues from across different business functions;
Knowledge of project management methodologies and techniques;
Knowledge of the development lifecycle of data reports and dashboards;
Excellent written and verbal communication skills, and the ability to explain technical analysis to a non-technical audience;
Ability to run workshops with clients, gathering requirements and translating them to scoping documents;
Ability to write procedural documents and conduct training; and
Engaging with key stakeholders and relaying information in a way that is easy to understand and provides commercial (not just process orientated) insights.

Desirable skills/attributes
Power BI experience, specifically the ability to design calculations in DAX which are accurate, clear and performant;
Ability to know when to create calculated columns and measures in Power BI;
Experience in the creation of nested conditional formulas;
Work experience in data visualisation or data analytics;
Recognised project management qualifications, such as PRINCE2, PMP, Agile, Scrum, Lean Six Sigma, etc.;
Proven experience in other analytics and BI platforms e.g. Alteryx, Tableau, IBM Cognos, SAP Business Objects;
Experience in the following industry sectors will be of specific interest: energy/utilities, life sciences and healthcare; and
Azure Modern Data Platform and SQL Server Reporting Services knowledge is an advantage.
